#: ../../S/spawn.rst:5
msgid "spawn"
msgstr "spawn"

#: ../../S/spawn.rst:7
msgid "n\\.,vi\\."
msgstr "名詞・自動詞"

#: ../../S/spawn.rst:10
msgid ""
"[techspeak] In Unix parlance, to create a child process from within a "
"process. Technically this is a ‘fork’; the term ‘spawn’ is a bit more "
"general and is used for threads (lightweight processes) as well as "
"traditional heavyweight processes."
msgstr ""
"[techspeak] "
"Unixの言葉遣いで、あるプロセスの中から子プロセスを作ること。技術的にはこれは‘fork(フォーク)’だ。‘spawn’という用語はもう少し一般的で、伝統的なヘビーウェイトのプロセスだけでなく、スレッド(ライトウェイトのプロセス)にも使われる。"

#: ../../S/spawn.rst:14
msgid ""
"In gaming, meant to indicate where (spawn-point) and when a player comes to "
"life (or re-spawns) after being killed. Opposite of :ref:`frag`\\."
msgstr ""
"ゲームにおいて、プレイヤーが殺された後に生き返る(または再spawnする)場所(spawn-point)と時を示すのに使われる。\\ "
":ref:`frag`\\ の反対。"
